com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium

Class JSContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium.JSContext

  • public class JSContext
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents JavaScript execution context. Each frame on the web page has it's own execution context. JavaScript objects created in one context will not be visible and accessible in other contexts.

    JavaScript context is initialized and created automatically for each frame on the loaded web page only if this frame has JavaScript code. If frame doesn't have JavaScript code, context will not be created for this frame. To force context creation you can call Browser.executeJavaScriptAndReturnValue(long, String) method for required frame.

    When frame is reloaded or another web page is loaded, all existing contexts will be destroyed and new contexts will be created. To check whether context is destroyed call the isDisposed() method or use DisposeListener.
    表示JavaScript执行上下文。网页上的每个框架都有其自己的执行上下文。在一个上下文中创建的JavaScript对象在其他上下文中将不可见和不可访问。仅当此框架具有JavaScript代码时，才会为加载的网页上的每个框架自动初始化并创建JavaScript上下文。如果框架没有JavaScript代码，则不会为此框架创建上下文。要强制创建上下文，可以为所需框架调用Browser.executeJavaScriptAndReturnValue（long，String）方法。当重新加载框架或加载另一个网页时，所有现有上下文将被销毁并创建新的上下文。要检查上下文是否被破坏，请调用isDisposed（）方法或使用DisposeListener。
